ðŸ“– Legend & Scoring Explanation

ORKG Scoring System

The ORKG accuracy score is a position-weighted metric that rewards correct predictions appearing higher in the ranked list:

  • Rank 1 (Top-1 Match): 100% score - The correct field is the top prediction
  • Rank 2 or 3: 80% score - Correct field appears in positions 2-3
  • Rank 4 or 5: 60% score - Correct field appears in positions 4-5
  • Not in Top-5: 0% score - Correct field not found in top 5 predictions

Final score = Average of all paper scores. Higher is better.

Metrics Explained

  • Accuracy Score: ORKG position-weighted accuracy (see above)
  • Top-1 Accuracy: Percentage of papers where the first prediction is correct
  • Top-5 Accuracy: Percentage of papers where correct field appears in top 5
  • Avg H-Distance: Average hierarchical distance of top-1 predictions (lower is better)
  • Avg Response Time: Average time to get classification (lower is better)
  • Total Tokens: Total LLM tokens used (only for new classifiers)

Radar Chart Dimensions

  • Top-1/5 Accuracy: Direct accuracy percentage (0-100%)
  • ORKG Score: Position-weighted accuracy (0-100%)
  • Speed: Inverted response time (100 = fastest)
  • Token Efficiency: Inverted token usage (100 = fewest tokens)
  • Proximity (H-Dist): Inverted H-Distance (100 = closest to ground truth)

Hierarchical Distance

  • 0 = Exact match in taxonomy
  • 1-2 = Close (sibling fields)
  • 3+ = Distant (different branches)
